<h3>Dress and Grooming Standards</h3>
<p>At BYU&ndash;Idaho and in the Church, there is a great focus on the small and simple things. One of the small and simple things we have the privilege of participating in at BYU&ndash;Idaho is the Dress &amp; Grooming Standards. We have a charge to dress modestly and be groomed appropriately every day. Through your obedience, you will help create an environment in which the Holy Ghost can minister to and lift not only you, but also everyone around you.</p>
<p>Remember that shorts, capris, flip-flops, tight or revealing clothing, other inappropriate attire/styles, and unshaven faces for men, are not permitted on campus. In addition, Hart issue shorts may not be worn on campus except in the Hart Building or other approved recreational facilities. Students are required to adhere to normal Dress &amp; Grooming standards when coming to and from these facilities.</p>
<p>We encourage each of you to strengthen your commitment to the BYU&ndash;Idaho Honor Code by maintaining appropriate behavior, dress, and grooming standards while on campus.</p>
